=Bio=

"Mark Joób (born 1974) is Honorary Professor at the Faculty of Economics, University of West Hungary holding courses in the fields of Business ethics, Economic psychology and Economic sociology. He earned a PhD from the University of Zurich for his research on global justice. He worked nearly a year for a large Swiss bank. At present, he conducts research on democratic accountability of business and monetary reform at the Institute for Business Ethics, University of St. Gallen, Switzerland.

Mark Joób is member of the board of editors of the Hungarian Journal of Economy & Society. He is co-founder and member of the managing committee of the Swiss Association for Monetary Modernisation (www.vollgeld.ch) which aims at establishing a sovereign money system in Switzerland by means of a national plebiscite."

